{"_id":"01HAEgs3BWl0LJLY","name":"Selfless","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>You think of others before yourself. You sleep on the floor to give another the bed. You pretend to be full to give your friends the last bite of meat. You stand before your friends when the dragon breathes fire. You buy the book that everyone else in your adventuring party reads&mdash;a true hero!</p>\n<p>The extent and frequency of your sacrifice determines whether this is a Minor or Major Hindrance.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.g3ldDrRJkpVWozFZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_l6gm1g9aa6g"}}}
{"_id":"22mz6MkgQMRgUC68","name":"Doomed","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Death is eager for your hero. Perhaps she cheated it at some point in her path, or was brought back from the dead and owes the Ferryman a fee. Whatever the reason, the heroine subtracts 2 from Soak rolls.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7bfT6AIUw7nEwLsU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_r5spssrhnxs"}}}
{"_id":"9a31c0FfBVEOWzHZ","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isArcaneDevice":false,"arcaneSkillDie":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"powerPoints":{},"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"parry":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bf6w7lfm7uv","name":"Minor","color":"#8b160f","fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":"","sorting":"m","contents":["Y8Qz8J8OBmVv5QxW","rc5N1Ngelk0cuWzc","tIzTX3egp35NLLym"],"children":[]}}}
{"_id":"CBMmE5281u8KqaQL","name":"Arcane Sensitivity","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>A spell gone wrong, an old curse, a strange bloodline, or some other mishap caused your hero to be more susceptible to arcane energy than others.</p>\n<p>As a Minor Hindrance, subtract 2 when making a Trait roll to resist a power, including arcane creature abilities (GM&rsquo;s call). Subtract 4 as a Major Hindrance.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kzw32kvuaaU4CWvo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_l6gm1g9aa6g"}}}
{"_id":"G2VBy8W66nCr58Ip","name":"Material Components","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This Hindrance may only be taken by those with an Arcane Background.</p>\n<p>The spellcaster&rsquo;s abilities consume material items when activated. Maybe a wizard needs a piece of brimstone to cast a fireball (blast with a fire Trapping) or a priestess needs a splash of holy water for her goddess to grant smite.</p>\n<p>Such items are assumed to be at hand&mdash;usually in a pocket, bag, or convenient pouch. If the caster is ever stripped of her possessions and can&rsquo;t get the materials she needs, she can&rsquo;t activate her powers.</p>\n<p>A caster also runs out of material components (or it breaks, shatters, etc.) if she rolls a Critical Failure while casting.</p>\n<p>Replenishing components for spells of Novice or Seasoned Rank can usually be done between encounters as the character purchases or forages for more, or perhaps simply finds them &ldquo;at the bottom of her bag.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Components for Heroic or higher Rank powers are more difficult to replace. They require d20 x 1,000 gp, d4 day&rsquo;s worth of gathering or foraging with a Survival roll, a trip to an exotic bazaar, or whatever else the Game Master feels is appropriate for that campaign world.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AtXYVmg4zNYnbpsZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_r5spssrhnxs"}}}
{"_id":"KjEG8Bgc9R4qMKbk","name":"Talisman","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Only characters with an Arcane Background Edge can take this Hindrance. Because they are already dependent on physical objects for their powers, alchemists (see page 78) may not take this Hindrance.</p>\n<p>The caster is dependent on a physical item to activate his powers. The Talisman might be a magic staff, a sacred symbol, a wand, a weapon, or any other transportable item.</p>\n<p>When caught without it, the caster subtracts 1 from all arcane skill rolls (&ndash;2 as a Major Hindrance), and is Stunned if the roll is a Critical Failure.</p>\n<p>Replacing a lost Talisman depends on the object, but should usually require getting it back from whoever took it. If it was destroyed, the Game Master should work with the player to figure out what might make a suitable replacement and how it might be gained.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3eM7E2o76a74umws"},"cf":{"id":"temp_l6gm1g9aa6g"}}}
{"_id":"RKatCP7IVSTJsxpd","name":"Jingoistic","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The character dislikes people from other cultures and believes his own to be far superior&mdash;a snooty city dweller, for example, might dislike &ldquo;uncouth&rdquo; barbarians or the citizens of a rival city- state. He cannot help belittling other cultures at every opportunity.</p>\n<p>As a Minor Hindrance, the targets of his ire may not benefit from his Command Edges. He cannot keep from insulting them and subtracts 2 from Persuasion rolls when interacting with them. The penalty increases to &minus;4 for the Major Hindrance.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EIzBM5sPRhCl6PfH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_l6gm1g9aa6g"}}}
{"_id":"Y8Qz8J8OBmVv5QxW","name":"Amorous","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The character is easily enamored with a pretty face. Perhaps it&rsquo;s lust or lechery, or perhaps he just has a keen appreciation of natural beauty.</p>\n<p>Amorous characters suffer an additional &minus;2 penalty to resist Tricks and Tests of Will by any character with the Attractive or Very Attractive Edge.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MpbTOfu2VERQCuLY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bf6w7lfm7uv"}}}
{"_id":"Zs7nTOgJx3FJk7Lb","name":"Corruption","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This Hindrance may only be taken by a character with an Arcane Background.</p>\n<p>The caster&rsquo;s magic draws on some foul, evil, or tainted source. Whenever he rolls a Critical Failure on his arcane skill roll, he gains a new Minor Hindrance that reflects the corruption of his mind and body.</p>\n<p>A wizard might become Jealous, for example, as he realizes how difficult it is to gather his power. Or Ugly as those dark energies are reflected in his contorted features.</p>\n<p>These Hindrances last until the spell-user&rsquo;s next Advance, at which time he may remove one Minor Hindrance, or reduce a Major Hindrance to a Minor.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":true},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.agRqqjw2wk006SdK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_r5spssrhnxs"}}}
{"_id":"jQuXNr95eyQPWiVq","name":"Armor Interference","type":"hindrance","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Bulky armor interferes with some warriors&rsquo; fighting style or maneuverability, and the precise, intricate somatic movements required for certain types of spellcasting.</p>\n<p>Those with this Minor Hindrance subtract 4 from arcane skill rolls, Agility rolls, and Agility-based skill rolls if wearing medium or heavy armor, or using a medium or heavy shield. The character may wear cloth or light armor, or use light shields, without interference.</p>\n<p>As a Major Hindrance, the penalty also applies to light armor and shields.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"major":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UuSVhFoxfpgK3sp7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_l6gm1g9aa6g"}}}
